ift · heterogeneous formats · auditability · incremental and hybrid loads · cost &amp; latency.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr algn="l" marL="431799" indent="-215899" lvl="1"><a:lnSpc><a:spcPts val="3239"/></a:lnSpc><a:buFont typeface="Arial"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1999" spc="19"><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="000000"/></a:solidFill><a:latin typeface="Poppins"/><a:ea typeface="Poppins"/><a:cs typeface="Poppins"/><a:sym typeface="Poppins"/></a:rPr><a:t>Consequences: Adding a source becomes a row, not a release. Logic centralizes; configuration scales linearly with sources, not codepaths.</a:t></a:r></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp></p:spTree></p:cSld><p:clrMapOvr><a:masterClrMapping/></p:clrMapOvr></p:sld>